raw_data.description: Coffee shop located in the beautiful Refinery building with a full host of food/beverage offerings (including of course, our home roasted coffee). See you soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Their coffee is phenomenal! They roast--in house--and their attention to detail is unmatched.

Order: Cappuccino
Summary: Good coffee, but this is basically a stall. Not somewhere you‚Äôd want to hang out. Also, parking was stupidly expensive.

Review: I‚Äôve been to the other Queen City grounds location in years past, so when I was looking for some good coffee, I looked them up. Unfortunately, I didn‚Äôt realize this was a ‚Äúmini location‚Äù on the ground floor of some office buildings.
When we walked in, it quickly became apparent that my friend and I weren‚Äôt about to sit down and hang out. There was basically no sitting, and I‚Äôm assuming most people who come here are from the business above.
The coffee was great, but I wouldn‚Äôt go back here because I like to hang out when I go to coffee shops out of town. I could maybe see myself letting someone with me jump out of the car and order while I swung around to pick them up if I needed a quick fix.
Oh! And we spent maybe 15 minutes getting coffee, and the parking garage charged us $4. Insane.
First time here, mocha is fantastic!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Michael!  Happy to be your friendly, neighborhood mocha supplier üôÉ

reviews_data.review_text:
Our company LOVES QCG! The coffee is my favorite in Charlotte and all the baristas are fantastic. My go to is 1 pump vanilla + 1 pump caramel hot (or iced) latte, but the fall specials are always tasty too.

Their location in uptown (The Landing at Fourth Ward) has great brunch options - specifically the "Burrito You Want". Every time my family comes in town they want to go, and my dad is veryyyy specific about his coffee, he has 5 different coffee machines at home lol. Check it out!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow thanks for the expert endorsement Olivia!

reviews_data.review_text: I have been here twice and both times they were closed when saying it‚Äôs open
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Drew, we closed early today due to the storm and last Friday our barista had a family emergency.  Please reconsider and give us a chance to make it up to you

reviews_data.review_text: Barista was really nice and my latte was good! My only downfall was the somewhat limited options. Like the lack of a toaster & no cold foam. I think these are very simple but potentially greatly beneficial changes that could be made to improve the customer experience. I enjoy coffee shops with a bit more variety. But nonetheless it was still a good experience
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi there Lo - thank you for the feedback.  Our kitchen does have some limitations but we should‚Äôve been able to toast for you.  Also we do offer cold foam; apologies if you were informed otherwise!

reviews_data.review_text: My friend and I came to visit last Saturday for a couple of hours. We both enjoyed ourselves and I‚Äôll come back in the future.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Awesomeness!  Love to hear it!  Lots of fun events upcoming too if you‚Äôre looking for entertainment‚Ä¶ music tomorrow eve, comedy Saturday evening.

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee, food and friendly staff. The perfect place for remote work to get yourself out of the house and even enjoy a beer later in the evening.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Mark!  Cmon back often!

reviews_data.review_text: Favorite place to meet friends and have business gatherings!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Tracey! Our favorite place to meet you üòä

reviews_data.review_text: Cool trivia!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Troy, I hope you won!

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute coffee shop. Coffee and oatmeal was great. The young lady made my latte with precision and care. Very impressed
reviews_data.owner_answer: üíï So happy to hear, Amber!

reviews_data.review_text: great cold brew
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Andy, great is our starting point, let us know if anything you try is less!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee at all locations and good food at the one by Skyhouse! Wish the Morehead one was open on the weekends but other than that great place!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
I‚Äôm so sorry, Brittany!  Sometimes keeping up with various web searches and changes slip through the cracks and we recently determined Sunday‚Äôs just did not have sufficient foot traffic as everything else in that building is closed.  We are always workshopping new ideas and hope to build enough of a following from the neighborhood to justify longer weekend hours.  

Shoot me an email at matt@queencitygrounds.com and we‚Äôll make it up to you!

reviews_data.review_text: Not open when says it is ?

Very ok coffee. I work in this building for reference, I've had this place quite a few times. I just want a nice medium roast coffee I can drink every day but their black coffee has strange flavors and is extremely expensive for just a regular black coffee. Also they open at 7:30am, which is unusually late for a coffee shop in my opinion.
Great iced soy lattes and staff at this location.  I don't recall the woman's name who helped me, but she was very kind, talkative, and engaged.  Def recommend coming in for a quick sip.
Good vibes. Good coffee. Good cookies as well! Enjoyed my flat white
